Dataset

The dataset used in the report is the Englandâ€™s Immigrants 1330 - 1550 dataset, whih contains over 64,000 names of people known to have migrated to England during the period of the Hundred Yearsâ€™ War and the Black Death, the Wars of the Roses and the Reformation.

Feature Engineering

Total Wealth and Payable

Looking at the dataset, we can create two new features that are the sum of the wealth and payable features (wealth_total_l, wealth_total_s, wealth_total_d; wealth_payable_l, and wealth_payable_s, wealth_payable_d, respectively). This is due to Â£sd (pronounced Lsd) being the name for the pre-decimal currencies that were common throughout Europe.

  • L - pound
  • S - shilling
  • d - pence

According to Retrowow, there were 12 pence in a shilling and 20 shillings in a pound. Therefore, there were 240 pennies in a pound.

immigrants[c("wealth_total_l", "wealth_total_s", "wealth_total_d")][is.na(immigrants[c("wealth_total_l", "wealth_total_s", "wealth_total_d")])] <- 0

immigrants$wealth_total <- ((immigrants$wealth_total_l * 240) + (immigrants$wealth_total_s * 12) + immigrants$wealth_total_d)

immigrants$wealth_total[immigrants$wealth_total == 0] <- NA

immigrants <- subset(immigrants, select=-c(wealth_total_l, wealth_total_s, wealth_total_d))
ggplot(immigrants[!immigrants$gender == "Unknown",]) + 
  geom_density(aes(x = wealth_total, colour = gender)) + 
  labs(x = "Total Wealth (L+S+D)", y = "Relative Density", title = "Total Wealth by Gender") + 
  theme_classic()

ggplot(immigrants[!immigrants$gender == "Unknown",]) + 
  geom_density(aes(x = wealth_total, colour = gender)) + 
  labs(x = "Total Wealth (L+S+D)", y = "Relative Density", title = "Total Wealth by Gender") + 
  theme_classic() + 
  coord_cartesian(xlim = c(0, 1500))

immigrants[c("wealth_payable_l", "wealth_payable_s", "wealth_payable_d")][is.na(immigrants[c("wealth_payable_l", "wealth_payable_s", "wealth_payable_d")])] <- 0

immigrants$payable_total <- ((immigrants$wealth_payable_l * 240) + (immigrants$wealth_payable_s * 12) + immigrants$wealth_payable_d)

immigrants$payable_total[immigrants$payable_total == 0] <- NA

immigrants <- subset(immigrants, select=-c(wealth_payable_l, wealth_payable_s, wealth_payable_d))
ggplot(immigrants[!immigrants$gender == "Unknown",]) + 
  geom_density(aes(x = payable_total, colour = gender)) + 
  labs(x = "Total Payable (L+S+D)", y = "Relative Density", title = "Total Payable by Gender") + 
  theme_classic()

ggplot(immigrants[!immigrants$gender == "Unknown",]) + 
  geom_density(aes(x = payable_total, colour = gender)) + 
  labs(x = "Total Payable (L+S+D)", y = "Relative Density", title = "Total Payable by Gender") + 
  theme_classic() + 
  coord_cartesian(xlim = c(0, 50))

Residence Length

immigrants[c("residence_year", "residence_month")][is.na(immigrants[c("residence_year", "residence_month")])] <- 0

immigrants$residence_length <- ((immigrants$residence_year * 12) + immigrants$residence_month) / 12

immigrants$residence_length[immigrants$residence_length == 0] <- NA

immigrants <- subset(immigrants, select=-c(residence_year, residence_month))
ggplot(immigrants[!immigrants$gender == "Unknown",]) + 
  geom_density(aes(x = residence_length, colour = gender)) + 
  labs(x = "Years in England", y = "Relative Density", title = "Residence Length in England by Gender") + 
  theme_classic()

Exploration

Householder

immigrants$householder <- factor(immigrants$householder, levels = c("Yes", "No", "Unspecified", NA))

ggplot(data = immigrants[!is.na(immigrants$householder),], aes(x = householder, fill = gender)) + 
  geom_bar(position = "fill") + 
    scale_y_continuous(labels = percent_format()) + 
  labs(x = "Householder", y = "Percentage", fill = "Gender", title = "Percentage of Houshold Status by Gender")

ggplot(data = immigrants[!is.na(immigrants$householder) & !is.na(immigrants$social_statuses),], aes(x = householder, fill = social_statuses)) + 
  geom_bar(position = "fill") + 
  facet_wrap(~gender, scales = "free") + 
    scale_y_continuous(labels = percent_format()) + 
  labs(x = "Householder", y = "Percentage", fill = "Social Status", title = "Percentage of Houshold Status by Social Status") +
  geom_text_repel(position = position_fill(vjust = 0.5), stat='count',aes(label= social_statuses)) + 
  theme_classic()

house_occ_subset <- immigrants[,c("occupations","householder")]

house_occ <- aggregate(house_occ_subset, by = list(house_occ_subset$householder, house_occ_subset$occupations), FUN = length)

house_occ$Group.1 <- factor(house_occ$Group.1, levels = c("Yes", "No"))

house_occ <- house_occ[order(-house_occ$householder),] 

ggplot(data = house_occ[house_occ$householder >= 100,]) + 
  geom_bar(aes(x = reorder(Group.2, householder) , y = householder, fill = Group.1), stat = "identity") +
  facet_wrap(~Group.1) + 
  labs(x = "Occupation", y = "Number of People", fill = "Householder Status") + 
  coord_flip() + 
  theme_minimal() + 
  theme(strip.text.x = element_blank())

Wealth

wealth_transfer <- na.omit(aggregate(immigrants$wealth_total, by = list(immigrants$origin_region_standard, immigrants$residence_county), FUN = sum, no.rm = TRUE))

names(wealth_transfer) <- c("Origin", "Destination", "Wealth")

wealth_transfer$Origin_lat <- c(47.052505, 51.786726, 44.405650, 41.871940, 41.835682, 49.465691, 48.879870)

wealth_transfer$Origin_lon <- c(4.383721, 6.129540, 8.946256, 12.567380, -4.397636, -2.585278, 0.171253)

wealth_transfer$Destination_lat <- c(51.466994, 50.715559, 51.734331, 51.864211, 52.187247, 52.187247, 53.828472)

wealth_transfer$Destination_lon <- c(-1.185368, -3.530875, 0.469089, -2.238034, 0.970780, 0.970780, -1.578391)
worldmap <- borders("world", colour="#F2E8C8", fill="#6C6A6A") # create a layer of borders

all <- ggplot() + worldmap + 
 geom_curve(data=wealth_transfer, aes(x = Origin_lon, y = Origin_lat, xend = Destination_lon, yend = Destination_lat, size = Wealth), col = "#970027", curvature = .2, arrow = arrow(length = unit(0.04, "npc")), lineend = "round", ncp = 2000, alpha = 0.5, show.legend = FALSE) + 
  theme_classic() +

wealth_transfer_tble <- wealth_transfer[,1:3]

names(wealth_transfer_tble) <- c("Origin", "Residence", "Total Wealth (lsd)")

wealth_transfer_tble <- wealth_transfer_tble[order(-wealth_transfer_tble$`Total Wealth (lsd)`),]

tt1 <- ttheme_minimal()
